content.description:
Fun climb that's similar to Jizzleberry in overall character and difficulty, though the movement differs. Do them both!

Start with a fun boulder problem in a small depression, gaining a good obvious left hand flake leading to a no hands ledge. Some sequential movement using a sidepull and 2 finger pockets leads to a rest. Chill for a sec, then fire the crux through the next few bolts using a small knob, a good pinch, and some crimps, then get rewarded with a romp to the anchors.
content.location: Just left of Jizzleberry. Shares top 1/2 with Godfather Thang, which starts to the left in the crack.

content.description: Work up the crack system, avoiding or treading gingerly the X'ed blocks. Pull over to the low angle face then romp up the headwall on good pockets.
content.location: Just to the left of the right-most arete in Twizzler's Corner. Starts in a chalked up flake / corner.

climbs.name: The Jizzleberry Bush
climbs.fa: Equipped by JB Haab, 2014.  FA Mike Snyder, 2015

content.description: Is this the name of a new Jay-Z record?  Could be, but it's also a great rock climb.  Some fun, technical slab moves get you to a great rest where you have to make a very high clip.  Don't blow it!  From the rest, execute a fantastic, 3-bolt long boulder problem on beautiful, slightly overhung rock that ends at a great jug.  Easier (5.11 or so) climbing gets you to the chains.
content.location: Left of the big corner.  Rakkup app. has the best info

content.description:
A steep crack that begins left of but joins and ends with ‘Swamp Thang’

Have fun deciding on whether to lay it back or crack style it.

I will say that the obvious knee bar is very good.

Quality
content.location: steep crack to the left of Swamp Thang.

content.description: Follow a crack-like system over a bulge to a chill rest on less-than-vertical terrain. Push up the ever-steepening headwall on good holds.
content.location: Immediately right of the Booger 5 corner.

content.description: Head up the dark corner system. Lots of creative movement throughout.
content.location: The obvious corner / dihedral between Rap Stars and Mushroom Tip.
